.TH CAT-310DX_CORRELATE 1 "2026-04-05" "CAT-310DX Tools 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cat-310dx_correlate \- correlate CAT-310DX LPC clips with CAT-1000 clips by checksum
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B python3 cat-310dx_correlate.py
[\fB\-\-algo\fR \fIALGO\fR]
[\fB\-\-dx\-dir\fR \fIDIR\fR]
[\fB\-\-310dx\-wav\-dir\fR \fIDIR\fR]
[\fB\-\-cat1000\-dir\fR \fIDIR\fR]
[\fB\-\-cat1000\-wav\-dir\fR \fIDIR\fR]
[\fB\-o\fR \fIFILE\fR]
[\fB\-\-map\fR \fIFILE\fR]
[\fB\-q\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cat-310dx_correlate.py
performs two independent byte-for-byte checksum comparisons between
CAT-310DX clips and CAT-1000 clips:
.TP
.B LPC match
Compares \fB.lpc\fR files in the LPC directories.
.TP
.B WAV match
Compares \fB.wav\fR files in the WAV directories.
.PP
Both devices use MSB-first TMS5220-compatible LPC-10.
A checksum match indicates the same audio recording was used in both devices.
.PP
Two output files are produced in
.B tmp/
: a CSV correlation table and a JSON rename map
for use with
.BR cat-310dx_rename_clips.py (1).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-algo " ALGO"
Hash algorithm: \fBmd5\fR, \fBsha1\fR, or \fBsha256\fR.  Default: \fBsha256\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-dx\-dir " DIR"
Directory of CAT-310DX \fB.lpc\fR files.  Default: \fBcat-310dx_lpc_clips\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-310dx\-wav\-dir " DIR"
Directory of CAT-310DX \fB.wav\fR files.  Default: \fBcat-310dx_wav_clips\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-cat1000\-dir " DIR"
Directory of CAT-1000 \fB.lpc\fR files.  Default: \fBcat-1000_lpc_clips\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-cat1000\-wav\-dir " DIR"
Directory of CAT-1000 \fB.wav\fR files.  Default: \fBcat-1000_wav_clips\fR.
.TP
.BI \-o " FILE"
Output CSV file.  Default: \fBtmp/cat-310dx_correlation.csv\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-map " FILE"
Output JSON rename map.  Default: \fBtmp/cat-310dx_rename_map.json\fR.
.TP
.B \-q
Suppress per-file progress output.
.SH OUTPUT
.SS tmp/cat-310dx_correlation.csv
One row per CAT-310DX \fB.lpc\fR file with columns:
.IR dx_filename ,
.IR dx_size ,
.IR algo ,
.IR lpc_checksum ,
.IR lpc_match " (yes/no),"
.IR lpc_cat1000_filename ,
.IR lpc_cat1000_word_id ,
.IR lpc_cat1000_label ,
.IR wav_checksum ,
.IR wav_match " (yes/no/n\|/a),"
.IR wav_cat1000_filename ,
.IR wav_cat1000_word_id ,
.IR wav_cat1000_label ,
.IR match_type " (both/lpc_only/wav_only/conflict/none)."
.SS tmp/cat-310dx_rename_map.json
Maps old-style address-named basenames (e.g. \fB4FED_w01\fR) to label-tagged
basenames (e.g. \fB4FED_w01_One\fR) for each matched clip.  Consumed by
.BR cat-310dx_rename_clips.py (1).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run with defaults (sha256, standard directories):
.B python3 cat-310dx_correlate.py
.TP
Use MD5:
.B python3 cat-310dx_correlate.py \-\-algo md5
.TP
Custom directories and output files:
.B python3 cat-310dx_correlate.py \-\-dx\-dir clips/ \-\-cat1000\-dir cat-1000_lpc_clips/ \-o out.csv \-\-map map.json
.SH NOTES
Clips extracted with the updated
.B cat-310dx_extract.py
already carry sequence-numbered names such as \fB0001_One.lpc\fR and typically
do not need renaming even if a checksum match is found.  The rename map is
primarily useful for old-style address-named clips.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cat-310dx_extract (1),
.BR cat-310dx_rename_clips (1),
.BR cat-1000_lpc_export (1)
